Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek Black Polychrome pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; dull orange fabric with large quantity of gold mica inclusions; exterior: part of frieze of incised tongues alternately added white, black and added red (appearing dull orange); below, white-red-white-red-white band.
Curator's comments: Thicker, more micaceous fabric than other sherds in the 1888,0601.573 sequence
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.256, no.5)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.53)
